    <section ids="compute" names="compute">
        <title>Compute</title>
        <paragraph>The OpenStack Compute service allows you to control an
            Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS) cloud computing platform.  It gives you
            control over instances and networks, and allows you to manage access to the
            cloud through users and projects.</paragraph>
        <paragraph>Compute does not include virtualization software. Instead, it defines drivers
            that interact with underlying virtualization mechanisms that run on your host
            operating system, and exposes functionality over a web-based API.</paragraph>
